{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Pin down ordering guarantee for most-recent-N window with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f5bb27ae5114b9bab","f900ad6d63ff66c12"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"ordering guarantee for most-recent-N window"},{"coaching":"Pin down adverse post-claim edit class enumeration with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f6668a518d13cf6a5"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"adverse post-claim edit class enumeration"},{"coaching":"Plan how emit AC proof command completeness will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f02110bbe68e27a7e","f34b0ad575700db23","fbfff8d33b74dc258"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"emit AC proof command completeness"},{"coaching":"Realign blocking-FP proxy definition alignment with parent to the parent's plan — the parent wins on conflict; if the parent is genuinely wrong, update the PARENT first (which forces its re-review), never silently diverge the leaf.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f0a363b463043afbd"],"move_id":"13","move_name":"realign to parent plan","subject":"blocking-FP proxy definition alignment with parent"},{"coaching":"Plan how anchoring of the 4/8 grep verification command will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f4b6efd4e8b2eff3e"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"anchoring of the 4/8 grep verification command"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":8,"blocking":1,"dropped":13,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","probed":6,"ran":true,"references":6,"resolved":2,"status":"pass","unresolved_or_abstained":4},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":7773,"file_impact":2,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":0,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":6,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"pass","verify_commands_linted":50,"verify_lint_abstained":49},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":1961,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":2,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"floored_criteria":["E2","E6"],"floored_finding_ids":["f4b6efd4e8b2eff3e","fbfff8d33b74dc258"],"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":277.1,"llm_calls":28,"llm_ms":683013.9,"total_ms":683429.7,"verify_requests":37},"narrowed":true,"remediation":{"baseline":"sidecar","eligible":true,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":true,"plan_changed":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"sidecar_baseline":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","G7","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","G5","T2","T4","T5b","T5e","T6","T7","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify the `mine_outcome_corpus` import contract: either (a) document the `sys.path` manipulation needed and acknowledge the `sys.exit()` floor-check behavior (wrapping in a subprocess or `try/except SystemExit`), or (b) extract `build_corpus()` into a library-safe form that raises rather than calls `sys.exit()`.","cohort":["E4"],"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'rebuilds the outcome corpus from live store history by **importing `mine_outcome_corpus` as a module** (not a fork) and calling its build entry'","mine_outcome_corpus.py:381: `sys.exit(f'tickets history incomplete: recovered ...')` — uses sys.exit(), not raise","No `__init__.py` found in docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/","No existing file in the repo imports mine_outcome_corpus (grep returns no matches)","ABSENCE: no plan acknowledgment of the sys.exit() hazard or import-path setup required"],"finding":"`mine_outcome_corpus.build_corpus()` calls `sys.exit()` on floor-check failure (mine_outcome_corpus.py:381), not `raise SystemExit` or a domain exception. The plan asserts the new job 'imports `mine_outcome_corpus` as a module and calling its build entry,' but calling `sys.exit()` from within an imported module terminates the calling process (`gate_eval_instrumentation.py`) rather than propagating a catchable exception. The harnesses directory also has no `__init__.py`, so the import requires path manipulation. No existing harness currently imports `mine_outcome_corpus`.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f163868557e70ce81","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'rebuilds the outcome corpus from live store history by importing `mine_outcome_corpus` as a module'; mine_outcome_corpus.py:381","norm_id":"nb3950aeb50a36178","priority":0.7556,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["If the git-object walk recovers fewer than 500 reviewed tickets (e.g. in a CI environment with a shallow clone), `build_corpus()` calls `sys.exit()` and terminates `gate_eval_instrumentation.py` without a catchable error, making `--verify-repro` fail silently rather than with a useful error message.","The implementer must either add `sys.path` manipulation to import the script, or the Scope/AC must specify the import mechanism; without this the integration is ambiguous."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Add to the Scope section: 'The harness imports `mine_outcome_corpus` via `importlib.util.spec_from_file_location`; floor-check failure from `build_corpus()` propagates as `SystemExit` and should be caught and re-raised as a descriptive `RuntimeError` so `--verify-repro` produces a clear diagnostic rather than a silent exit.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.8889,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"low","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify what field determines 'most-recent N reviews' for the `--window N` trailing window (e.g., add a `latest_review_ts_ns` column to the outcome corpus, or document that recency is proxied by the sidecar file's ns-prefix timestamp from `all_review_results`).","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'over the most-recent N reviews, default N=200'","Outcome corpus schema (mine_outcome_corpus.py:10): fields are ticket_id, ticket_type, level, post_claim_edit_class, reopen_count, force_close, completion_verifier_fail_count, review_round_count, had_persisted_review — no timestamp column","all_review_results() orders newest-first WITHIN a ticket only (sidecar.py:164), not across all reviewed tickets","ABSENCE: no specification of which field determines 'recency' for cross-ticket window ordering"],"finding":"The `--window N` 'most-recent N reviews' ordering is mechanistically underspecified: the outcome corpus schema (as produced by `build_corpus()`) contains no timestamp field, so 'most-recent N' has no resolvable ordering criterion across tickets. The AC requires `--window N` to yield a strict subset, but without a cross-ticket sort key the implementer must guess (e.g., alphabetical by ticket_id, or by sidecar file timestamp read separately) — two implementers could produce different subsets.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f5bb27ae5114b9bab","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — per-criterion trailing metrics definition; AC: '`--window N` bounds the trailing window and is exercised by the golden test (a smaller N yields a subset)'","norm_id":"n383f4ff86087d0ee","priority":0.5863,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer sorts by ticket_id (alphabetical) → window is deterministic but meaningless as a 'recent' proxy","Implementer reads sidecar file timestamps per ticket for ordering → requires a separate pass and is undocumented","The golden test passes with any consistent sort but the metric values would differ depending on chosen ordering, undermining the alarm utility"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Add a `latest_review_ts_ns` column to `build_corpus()` / `build_row()` (taken from the most-recent REVIEW_RESULT blob timestamp in the git-walk event store, already available in the blobs as `ts`). The gate-eval job then sorts by this column descending and takes the first N rows. Document this in the Scope section.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a co-located definition in the metrics section specifying exactly which `post_claim_edit_class` values count as 'adverse' for the blocking-FP proxy denominator (e.g., `∈ {plan-authored-post-claim, operator-attested-retag, ac-strengthened, substantive-unclassified}` — the `_SUBSTANTIVE_CLASSES` set minus cosmetic).","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'no corresponding adverse post-claim edit' — the word 'adverse' is used without enumeration","mine_outcome_corpus.py _CLASS_PRECEDENCE = ['plan-authored-post-claim','operator-attested-retag','ac-strengthened','substantive-unclassified','cosmetic','none']","_SUBSTANTIVE_CLASSES in mine_outcome_corpus.py excludes 'cosmetic' — implementer could interpret either way","The plan defines 'adverse' nowhere else in the metric section"],"finding":"The blocking_fp_proxy denominator uses the phrase 'no corresponding adverse post-claim edit' but never defines which post_claim_edit_class values count as 'adverse'. The miner's closed vocabulary has 6 values (plan-authored-post-claim, operator-attested-retag, ac-strengthened, substantive-unclassified, cosmetic, none). An implementer must decide: does 'adverse' mean any non-'none', or only substantive classes (excluding 'cosmetic'), or only the 3 classes also used in §5.2's substantive set? The plan's metric definition section is missing this co-located decision rule.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6668a518d13cf6a5","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Per-criterion trailing metrics', blocking-FP proxy(C) definition","norm_id":"n3bd8a447e0d4b3f4","priority":0.5863,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer counts 'cosmetic' edits as 'adverse' → blocking_fp_proxy denominator is over-inclusive, understating the FP rate","An implementer treats only the 3 §5.2 semantic classes as 'adverse' → different denominator than the 6-class or 5-class interpretation","The golden test fixture asserts schema non-triviality but does not pin the adverse-class interpretation, so two correct-looking implementations can produce silently divergent metrics"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"In the 'blocking-FP proxy(C)' bullet, replace 'no corresponding adverse post-claim edit' with 'post_claim_edit_class ∈ {\"none\", \"cosmetic\"}' (i.e., no substantive post-claim edit) — mirroring the _SUBSTANTIVE_CLASSES set already used by the miner.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the sort key for '--window N': either define a secondary timestamp field to add to the outcome corpus rows, or explicitly state that 'most-recent' means highest `review_round_count` tickets, or that the corpus is sorted by the git-walk timestamp of the first REVIEW_RESULT event per ticket.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Confirmed outcome corpus schema from runs/outcome_corpus.jsonl line 1: no timestamp field present","mine_outcome_corpus.py build_corpus() returns rows sorted by ticket_id (alphabetical), not by any temporal field","Plan text: 'most-recent N reviews' — no sort key specified","The sidecar all_review_results returns newest-first (by filename ns-timestamp), but that is per-ticket, not a global ordering of the corpus"],"finding":"The '--window N bounds the trailing window' feature is specified as 'most-recent N reviews, default N=200', but the outcome corpus schema (ticket_id, ticket_type, level, post_claim_edit_class, reopen_count, force_close, completion_verifier_fail_count, review_round_count, had_persisted_review) contains no timestamp field. The plan gives no specification of the sort key that defines 'most-recent', leaving the windowing algorithm mechanistically undefined.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f900ad6d63ff66c12","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Per-criterion trailing metrics (over the most-recent N reviews, default N=200)'; AC — '--window N bounds the trailing window'","norm_id":"n82be180fffb2b848","priority":0.5863,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer sorts by ticket_id (alphabetical) — 'most-recent' becomes lexicographic, not temporal","Implementer sorts by review_round_count or reopen_count as a proxy — semantically wrong","The --window golden test in test_gate_eval_classifier.py checks 'a smaller N yields a subset' but cannot validate correctness of which subset without a defined sort key","Two runs on different corpus snapshots produce different 'most-recent N' populations if the sort order is undefined"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Strengthen the `--emit` proving command to assert all three promised fields are present: `assert d and all('blocking_fp_proxy' in v and 'advisory_application_rate' in v for v in d.values() if v)`","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6","F1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC text: 'a non-trivial object with ≥1 criterion carrying a computed advisory_application_rate, blocking_fp_proxy, and sample counts'","Proving command checks only: `any('blocking_fp_proxy' in v for v in d.values())` — advisory_application_rate and sample counts are not asserted"],"finding":"The `--emit` proving command only asserts the presence of `blocking_fp_proxy` but the AC text explicitly requires three fields — `advisory_application_rate`, `blocking_fp_proxy`, AND sample counts — all be present and non-null; an implementation that omits `advisory_application_rate` or sample counts would still pass the proving command.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f02110bbe68e27a7e","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — `--emit` AC proving command: `python -c \"import json;d=json.load(open('...'));assert d and any('blocking_fp_proxy' in v for v in d.values())\"`","norm_id":"ne8559e55700069e1","priority":0.55,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An executor implements only blocking_fp_proxy, skips advisory_application_rate, the CI proving command turns green, and the partial implementation ships undetected."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Replace the single-field check with: `python -c \"import json; d=json.load(open('docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/gate_eval_metrics.json')); assert d and any('blocking_fp_proxy' in v and 'advisory_application_rate' in v for v in d.values()), 'missing required metric fields'\"`","tier":"LLM","validity":1.0,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Update the parent epic's (6982-2e75-f8fa-43b9) Success Criteria to replace the 'measured against E1's committed finding-adjudication ground-truth corpus' clause with the outcome-corpus-signal proxy definition before re-reviewing this leaf, so the leaf's blocking-FP proxy definition is a consistent narrowing of the parent's updated contract rather than a contradiction of it.","cohort":["G7"],"criteria":["G7"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent Success Criteria: 'the blocking-FP proxy for a criterion is the fraction of that criterion's BLOCKING findings, over a trailing window of reviews, that are subsequently adjudicated false-positive / not-block-worthy — measured by R7's instrumentation against E1's committed finding-adjudication ground-truth corpus; 10% is the demotion threshold'","Leaf What: 'blocking-FP proxy(C) = (# tickets where C surfaced ≥1 blocking finding AND that ticket was subsequently adjudicated not-block-worthy — proxied by force_close OR reopen_count>0 OR no corresponding adverse post-claim edit) / (# tickets where C surfaced ≥1 blocking finding)'","Leaf Scope: no file or step references E1's adjudication corpus; the adjudication corpus is entirely absent from the leaf's deliverables and computation","Parent's plan text has not been updated to reflect the E1 adjudication-corpus invalidation described in comments — the authoritative contract still specifies adjudication-corpus-based measurement"],"finding":"The leaf redefines the blocking-FP proxy measurement mechanism in a way that contradicts the parent's Success Criteria. The parent (6982-2e75-f8fa-43b9) states the proxy is 'measured by R7's instrumentation against E1's committed finding-adjudication ground-truth corpus,' but the leaf defines it using outcome-corpus signals (force_close, reopen_count, no corresponding adverse post-claim edit) with no involvement of the finding-adjudication corpus.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f0a363b463043afbd","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"Parent Success Criteria ('measured by R7's instrumentation against E1's committed finding-adjudication ground-truth corpus'); Leaf What section ('blocking-FP proxy(C) = … proxied by force_close OR reopen_count>0 OR no corresponding adverse post-claim edit') and Scope/AC sections (no mention of adjudication corpus)","norm_id":"n3fbbc7fa13287c0c","priority":0.425,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer follows the leaf and ships an outcome-signal proxy, satisfying the leaf's ACs but failing the parent's stated Success Criteria for R7 dogfood monitoring.","A later epic-level review flags R7 as non-compliant with the parent, requiring a retrofit or re-review cycle."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"In the parent epic, revise the Success Criteria blocking-FP proxy definition to read: '…measured by R7's instrumentation against the E1 outcome corpus (post-claim edits, reopens, force-closes) — the finding-adjudication corpus was invalidated (see E1 descope note) and is not used; 10% is the demotion threshold.' Once the parent is updated (staling its plan-review attestation) and re-reviewed, the leaf's definition becomes a compliant subset.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"low","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E5"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The `--emit` AC is satisfiable by an implementation that writes a trivially wrong or empty metrics JSON (e.g., `{}`, all-zero values, missing criteria keys), because the only assertion is 'writes the metrics file and exits 0'. The metric aggregation logic — computing advisory-application rate and blocking-FP proxy from the join — is new, non-trivial arithmetic that is not covered by `--verify-repro` (which only checks per-ticket classification, not aggregated ratios). The primary output of the job (the per-criterion metrics) thus has no correctness check.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f34b0ad575700db23","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — first AC bullet (`--emit` proving command) and `--verify-repro` AC bullet","norm_id":"nf041e6d0514c32fe","priority":0.4125,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Extend `--verify-repro` to also run `--emit` over the 8 frozen-case fixture and assert that (a) the output JSON contains at least the criteria exercised by those 8 cases, (b) blocking-FP proxy and advisory-application rate for those criteria fall within expected ranges (or equal hand-computed values from the 8 cases). This keeps the test hermetic and exercises the full aggregation path.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify how `gate_eval_instrumentation.py` resolves the `mine_outcome_corpus` import — either add `__init__.py` to harnesses/ (making it a package), insert a `sys.path` manipulation at the top of the new file, or use `importlib` with an explicit path (and state which approach in Scope).","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/ has no __init__.py (confirmed via list_directory)","mine_outcome_corpus.py is a standalone script with `if __name__ == '__main__'` guard; it is not installed as part of the rebar package","resolve_symbol for 'build_corpus' in the harnesses module path returns UNRESOLVED","No existing harness in the directory imports another harness as a module (build_adjudication_corpus.py does not import mine_outcome_corpus)"],"finding":"The plan states the new job will work 'by importing `mine_outcome_corpus` as a module … calling its build entry', but `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/` has no `__init__.py` and is not installed as a package. A bare `import mine_outcome_corpus` (or `from mine_outcome_corpus import build_corpus`) in `gate_eval_instrumentation.py` will fail with `ModuleNotFoundError` unless `sys.path` is manipulated at runtime. The plan never specifies how this import is resolved.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"facf4f9aacb66380c","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'imports `mine_outcome_corpus` as a module … calling its build entry'","norm_id":"nb83d4667ea62068c","priority":0.2347,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer writes `from mine_outcome_corpus import build_corpus` in gate_eval_instrumentation.py; it raises ModuleNotFoundError when run from any directory other than harnesses/ without sys.path setup.","`make test` runs pytest which will fail to import the test file if it transitively depends on this unresolvable import."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a single line at the top of gate_eval_instrumentation.py: `sys.path.insert(0, os.path.dirname(__file__))` before the mine_outcome_corpus import, and note this in the Scope section.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.8889,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the import mechanism for `mine_outcome_corpus` in the harness (e.g., `importlib.util.spec_from_file_location` or a `sys.path.insert(0, Path(__file__).parent)` preamble), so the non-installed harness script is importable when `gate_eval_instrumentation.py` is run from any working directory.","cohort":["T3"],"criteria":["T3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'importing `mine_outcome_corpus` as a module (not a fork) and calling its build entry'","mine_outcome_corpus.py is located at docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/mine_outcome_corpus.py — not in src/ or any installed package","build_corpus() verified to exist at mine_outcome_corpus.py:377 (Partially-verified: function exists, import path unspecified)","No __init__.py or setup.cfg/pyproject.toml entry found in the harnesses/ directory making it a package"],"finding":"The plan says the job will import `mine_outcome_corpus` as a module, but `mine_outcome_corpus.py` lives in `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/` — a non-installed harness directory not on the default `sys.path`. The plan does not specify the import mechanism (e.g., `importlib.util.spec_from_file_location`, a `sys.path.insert`, or making the harness a package). A bare `import mine_outcome_corpus` in the new script will raise `ModuleNotFoundError` at runtime unless the import path is established.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f1d12428d2cdca42d","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'importing `mine_outcome_corpus` as a module (not a fork) and calling its build entry'","norm_id":"nc780a2a9937499b0","priority":0.2347,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Developer runs `python docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/gate_eval_instrumentation.py --verify-repro` from repo root — `import mine_outcome_corpus` fails with ModuleNotFoundError because the harnesses/ directory is not on sys.path.","CI runs the proving command and the import fails silently or loudly before any classification logic executes."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add to the top of `gate_eval_instrumentation.py`: `import sys, pathlib; sys.path.insert(0, str(pathlib.Path(__file__).parent))` before `import mine_outcome_corpus`, or use `importlib.util.spec_from_file_location('mine_outcome_corpus', Path(__file__).parent / 'mine_outcome_corpus.py')`.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.8889,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify in the harness design (Scope section or inline code comment) that `has_strong_finding` imports `RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY` from `rebar.llm.plan_review.sidecar` rather than hardcoding `0.5`, so the predicate stays in sync with the gate's own bar automatically.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"the 0.5 floor is the codebase's own `RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY` (`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py:299`)\"","Plan references the constant by value (0.5) without specifying import vs. literal — the harness spec is silent on this."],"finding":"The `has_strong_finding` predicate anchors its `priority >= 0.5` floor to `RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY` at `sidecar.py:299`, but the plan does not specify whether the harness *imports* that constant or hardcodes the literal `0.5`. If hardcoded, any future change to `RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY` in the source silently diverges the classifier's strength bar from the gate's own bar, breaking the predicate's semantic alignment without a test failure.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fc5aec772f5d986c6","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"## What — `has_strong_finding` definition; Scope — `gate_eval_instrumentation.py`","norm_id":"ne2e17c76452c63db","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY is tuned upward (e.g., to 0.6) during calibration; the harness still uses 0.5, silently under-counting strong findings and inflating MISSED classifications with no test catching the drift."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In `gate_eval_instrumentation.py`, replace the literal `0.5` with `from rebar.llm.plan_review.sidecar import RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY` and use that name in the predicate. Add a note to the Scope bullet for `gate_eval_instrumentation.py` stating this import requirement.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] In the `docs/plan-review-gate.md` playbook section, add the repo-relative path to `criteria_routing.json` and a one-line example of the demotion edit (or a cross-reference to where the config schema is documented) so the operator response step is self-contained.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"demote it from blocking to advisory via an ordinary `criteria_routing.json` edit (`default_posture: \\\"advisory\\\"`)\"","No file path or schema reference is provided for criteria_routing.json in the plan text."],"finding":"The demotion playbook in `docs/plan-review-gate.md` tells an operator to respond to a >10% blocking-FP alarm by editing `criteria_routing.json` with `default_posture: \"advisory\"`, but neither the plan nor the target doc anchors where `criteria_routing.json` lives in the repo or references its schema. An operator encountering the alarm for the first time cannot complete the response step without additional searching.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f1c7e6fcd247b85fe","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"## What — Alarm/demotion rule; Acceptance Criteria — docs/plan-review-gate.md bullet","norm_id":"n8797edf3908b5152","priority":0.0825,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A new team member follows the playbook after a >10% alarm fires but cannot locate criteria_routing.json or confirm the correct key name without grepping the repo."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a sentence such as: 'Edit `config/criteria_routing.json` (schema: each criterion key maps to `{\"default_posture\": \"advisory\"|\"block\"}`) — set the offending criterion's `default_posture` to `\"advisory\"` and commit through the normal review flow.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify that `--emit` writes atomically (e.g., write to a `.tmp` file then `os.replace`) and document idempotency: a re-run always produces a complete, valid output file.","cohort":["T5b","T6","T9"],"criteria":["T5b"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan says `--emit` writes the per-criterion metrics to the file but specifies no atomic write strategy (write-to-temp-then-rename, or similar).","No mention of idempotency or partial-state safety for the write operation.","AC proving command does `json.load(open(...))` — this will silently return stale data or raise on a partially written file."],"finding":"The `--emit` write to `runs/gate_eval_metrics.json` is not specified as atomic. A crash or interruption mid-write will leave a corrupt/partial JSON file that subsequent reads will silently mis-parse, with no recovery path specified.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f011763e7483df2dd","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section / AC: `--emit` writes to `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/gate_eval_metrics.json`","norm_id":"n754f6ba6a29f6cbc","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Job is killed mid-write (OOM, Ctrl-C, CI timeout); next invocation or reader sees truncated JSON and either crashes or (worse) silently uses stale data."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Write to `gate_eval_metrics.json.tmp`, validate it's valid JSON, then `os.replace(tmp, target)` — standard atomic-write pattern; add a brief note in the Scope section.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add error-handling specification for `mine_outcome_corpus` and `sidecar.all_review_results` calls: define the exit code, log message, and (where appropriate) graceful degradation (e.g., emit partial metrics with a `data_complete: false` flag) when either dependency is unavailable or raises.","cohort":["T5b","T6","T9"],"criteria":["T5b"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan specifies the happy-path call sequence but contains no mention of try/except, graceful degradation, or informative error messages for these two calls.","No observability (log line, metric, or exit-code contract) is specified for the failure paths of these calls."],"finding":"No error handling is specified for the two external dependencies the job calls: (a) `mine_outcome_corpus` module import/call (can fail if the module API changes or the store is unavailable) and (b) `rebar.llm.plan_review.sidecar.all_review_results` (can fail if the sidecar store is inaccessible or returns unexpected schema). Neither error path is surfaced or logged.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3849d985ff492f13","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: '(a) rebuilds the outcome corpus … by importing `mine_outcome_corpus` as a module', '(b) reads each reviewed ticket's persisted `REVIEW_RESULT` sidecars via `rebar.llm.plan_review.sidecar.all_review_results`'","norm_id":"n044227f392714fd6","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Store is temporarily unavailable: job silently emits empty metrics or crashes with an unhandled exception and no actionable message.","Module API changes between E1 and R7 land: import error surfaces as an opaque traceback rather than a clear diagnostic."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Enumerate the intended consumers of `gate_eval_metrics.json` (e.g., 'operator reads manually; no automated consumer in this ticket') and document whether old files are overwritten or versioned, so the lifecycle is complete.","cohort":["T5b","T6","T9"],"criteria":["T9"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan defines who CREATES (the `--emit` flag) but does not enumerate consumers of the output file.","No concurrency control (file lock, PID guard) is specified for simultaneous `--emit` runs.","No RETIRE path: the file accumulates indefinitely or is silently clobbered — unclear which."],"finding":"`gate_eval_metrics.json` consumers are not enumerated, and no RETIRE/cleanup path is defined. The file will be unconditionally overwritten each `--emit` run with no concurrency control, and it is unclear whether any downstream consumer (dashboard, CI check, operator) reads a stale copy.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f51029b4cb669282d","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section: `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/gate_eval_metrics.json`; AC: `--emit` proving command","norm_id":"nab5b40cdba967600","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Two CI jobs run `--emit` concurrently; interleaved writes produce a corrupt file (overlapping with T5b write-atomicity gap).","An operator reads `gate_eval_metrics.json` expecting fresh data but receives a months-old file because the job silently failed; no staleness signal."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify validation and user-facing error messages for `--window N` (reject N≤0 with a clear message) and define `--emit`'s output and exit behaviour when the corpus yields zero qualifying tickets (e.g., write `{}` and exit 0 with a warning, or exit non-zero).","cohort":["T5b","T6","T9"],"criteria":["T6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan says `--window N` bounds the trailing window but gives no validation contract for invalid N values.","AC states the output must be 'non-trivial' on a fixture but does not specify what `--emit` outputs/exits when the live corpus has zero qualifying tickets.","No mention of user-facing error messages for invalid flag combinations."],"finding":"The CLI's `--window N` flag has no specified validation for edge-case inputs (N=0, N negative, N exceeding corpus size), and the `--emit` path has no specified behaviour when the outcome corpus is empty or yields zero qualifying tickets — the AC only enforces non-triviality on a fixture, not on live empty data.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f72a11e1dafa98151","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section: 'CLI flags `--verify-repro`, `--emit`, `--window N`'; AC: `--emit` proving command","norm_id":"n5c57bfa031f800d2","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["User passes `--window 0` or `--window -5`: tool either crashes with a Python exception or silently emits an empty metrics object indistinguishable from a valid zero-FP result.","Store is new/empty: `--emit` produces an all-null object that the AC assertion (`any('blocking_fp_proxy' in v ...)`) would reject, but the tool's own output/exit behaviour is unspecified."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Correct the module API reference: `mine_outcome_corpus` exposes `build_corpus()` (line 377), not `build_entry` — update the plan's What section and the harness spec to name the correct callable.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'importing `mine_outcome_corpus` as a module (not a fork) and calling its build entry'","mine_outcome_corpus.py:377: `def build_corpus() -> list[dict[str, Any]]:`","mine_outcome_corpus.py:508-514: `main()` calls `build_corpus()` — no `build_entry` defined anywhere in the file","ABSENCE: no `build_entry` symbol found in the harnesses directory search"],"finding":"The plan asserts the harness will import `mine_outcome_corpus` and call its 'build entry,' but no such entry-point function exists in the module. The actual public callable is `build_corpus()` (mine_outcome_corpus.py:377); `main()` at line 508 calls `build_corpus()` directly. There is no `build_entry` symbol.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f24f8efbd9eae45b5","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'importing `mine_outcome_corpus` as a module (not a fork) and calling its build entry'","norm_id":"n31ba76ef12570f13","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["The new harness `gate_eval_instrumentation.py` does `from mine_outcome_corpus import build_entry` and gets an ImportError at runtime, breaking both `--verify-repro` and `--emit`.","A developer following the plan spec writes the wrong import and the CI golden test silently passes only if it is mocked out, masking the broken live path."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Replace 'calling its build entry' with 'calling `build_corpus()`' throughout the plan, and have the harness do `from mine_outcome_corpus import build_corpus` (or `import mine_outcome_corpus; rows = mine_outcome_corpus.build_corpus()`).","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The plan's 'Outcome classification protocol' defines adverse post-claim edits as post_claim_edit_class ∈ {plan-authored-post-claim, ac-strengthened, substantive-unclassified}, but the frozen --verify-repro case 115b-ceea is asserted to be CAUGHT-BUT-IGNORED. The live outcome_corpus.jsonl (line 40) shows 115b-ceea has post_claim_edit_class='operator-attested-retag', which is NOT in the plan's adverse class set. Under the plan's own co-located decision rules, 115b-ceea would be classified N/A (no adverse edit), making the --verify-repro assertion for that case logically unreachable with the defined classifier.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f63ba1435c95ece1a","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Outcome classification protocol'; AC2 (--verify-repro, CAUGHT-BUT-IGNORED: 115b-ceea)","norm_id":"n1912f3c33ad71a98","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add `operator-attested-retag` to the adverse-class enumeration in the 'Outcome classification protocol' section, consistent with its inclusion in mine_outcome_corpus.py's `_SUBSTANTIVE_CLASSES`, or reclassify 115b-ceea as UNKNOWABLE/N/A in the AC2 frozen set and update the --verify-repro expected mapping.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The CAUGHT-BUT-IGNORED classification rule requires '≥1 substantive advisory finding' but 'substantive' is never defined as a filter predicate over the actual sidecar schema. The sidecar's build_payload stores findings with decision ∈ {\"block\", \"advisory\", \"dropped\", \"indeterminate\"} and a numeric priority field. There is no 'substantive' field. The plan's §5.2 prose reference ('did the gate say something substantive?') is not operationalized — does 'substantive advisory' mean decision==\"advisory\" (any advisory), or advisory AND priority ≥ some threshold, or advisory AND severity ∈ {\"major\", \"critical\"}, or advisory in SURFACED_DECISIONS (i.e., not dropped)?","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fdcbf1ff97c84fabe","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Outcome classification protocol': 'CAUGHT-BUT-IGNORED — the persisted review raised ≥1 substantive advisory finding'","norm_id":"n645af5da5cb1e074","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Replace 'substantive advisory finding' with 'surfaced advisory finding (decision==\"advisory\" and drop_reason is None)' throughout the classification protocol, matching the existing SURFACED_DECISIONS = (\"block\", \"advisory\") vocabulary in sidecar.py.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The plan states the new job 'imports/reuses mine_outcome_corpus.py, not a fork' to rebuild the outcome corpus, then also does a sidecar join reading per-finding criteria[] from REVIEW_RESULT blobs. But mine_outcome_corpus.py's _CONTENT_TYPES explicitly excludes REVIEW_RESULT — it is counted by UUID only, never blob-parsed. The plan never specifies how the new job reads REVIEW_RESULT blob *content* (criteria[], decision, findings) needed for the per-criterion join: does it extend load_events() to add REVIEW_RESULT to _CONTENT_TYPES, add a separate reader, or use on-disk sidecar files? These are architecturally incompatible choices with different retention properties.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f5a7f4da9aedae6e4","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'it imports/reuses mine_outcome_corpus.py, not a fork'; also the sidecar join spec 'per-finding criteria[] gives the per-criterion breakdown'","norm_id":"nf84e3c90b5dece56","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a sentence in Scope specifying that gate_eval_instrumentation.py extends load_events() to add REVIEW_RESULT to _CONTENT_TYPES (so the git-object walk also parses REVIEW_RESULT blob JSON for findings/criteria[]/decision), mirroring the compaction-proof approach the outcome corpus already uses.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The plan presents the UNKNOWABLE classification rule as 'deterministic' ('substantive-unclassified with a confound — force_close OR reopen_count>0'), but the one UNKNOWABLE frozen case (3006-e198) has post_claim_edit_class='ac-strengthened' in the outcome corpus (confirmed by the runs/README.md §5 re-verification table), not 'substantive-unclassified'. The stated deterministic rule cannot reproduce UNKNOWABLE for this case from corpus fields alone, contradicting the plan's assertion that the 8-case reproduction is fully mechanical. The ≥6/8 slack in AC2 is wide enough to tolerate this one miss, but the plan document and harnesses/README documentation would incorrectly claim the rules are fully deterministic when they require human semantic judgment for at least one case.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fea3aee4ce164c666","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Outcome classification protocol'; AC2 — '--verify-repro reproduces ... UNKNOWABLE: 3006-e198'","norm_id":"n99d684b929df48bb","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a hardcoded UNKNOWABLE annotation for 3006-e198 in the --verify-repro fixture (the §5.2 human judgment that this was UNKNOWABLE overrides the mechanical class), and document in the README that the UNKNOWABLE rule has one hardcoded historical exception whose human reasoning is recorded in §5.2.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"insufficient","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Tighten the AC5 grep to require the sidecar-signal context, e.g. `grep -q \"sidecar.*4/8\\|4/8.*sidecar\" docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/README.md` or anchor with the section heading.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Defect taxonomy item (1): substring false-positive — anchor with a word-boundary or quoted key","The string '4/8' is short and could appear in an unrelated context (e.g., a date, a ratio in a different discussion)."],"finding":"The AC5 proving command `grep -q \"4/8\" docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/README.md` is an unanchored substring match that would pass on any occurrence of '4/8' in the file — including in an unrelated sentence — without verifying that the 4/8 string appears in the context of the sidecar-signal finding.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4b6efd4e8b2eff3e","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — AC5 proving command: `grep -q \"4/8\" docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/README.md`","norm_id":"n12dd14ab497fcacb","priority":0.385,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A draft README that mentions '4/8' in a changelog note causes AC5 to pass even if the sidecar-signal finding section is entirely absent."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"grep -qE 'sidecar.{0,60}4/8|4/8.{0,60}sidecar' docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/README.md","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add to the `test_gate_eval_classifier.py` scope bullet an explicit statement that the file also includes a schema fixture (and its location/contents, e.g., a small synthetic metrics dict) asserting all three fields are present per the `--emit` AC.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6","E2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Scope: 'a golden test importing the pure classify and asserting the 8 frozen (cls, rounds, strong) → label tuples reproduce ≥6/8 (this is the CI-verifiable core; the full store integration is verified manually via --verify-repro)'","AC2: 'a schema assertion in the golden test enforces non-triviality on a fixture'","The fixture's location and contents are not defined in the Scope."],"finding":"The `--emit` AC states 'a schema assertion in the golden test enforces non-triviality on a fixture', but the Scope section describes `test_gate_eval_classifier.py` only as 'a golden test importing the pure `classify` and asserting the 8 frozen tuples reproduce ≥6/8' — the schema/fixture assertion for the `--emit` output is not listed as a deliverable in the Scope, leaving an unresolved gap between what the AC promises the test will do and what the Scope says it will contain.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fbfff8d33b74dc258","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope — `tests/unit/test_gate_eval_classifier.py` bullet vs. `--emit` AC text","norm_id":"n6966db9211fe1c1a","priority":0.198,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An executor implements test_gate_eval_classifier.py strictly from the Scope description (classify + window tests only), omitting the schema fixture, and the --emit AC's CI-verifiable non-triviality check never ships."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"1df663b4eb880ef8","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":277.1,"llm_calls":28,"llm_ms":683013.9,"total_ms":683429.7,"verify_requests":37},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591cc","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"plan_review_result_v2","ticket_id":"b1a4-af7a-4a48-465d","ticket_type":"story","verdict":"BLOCK","verified_at_sha":"43d1545237745f4666dcc13c81587c824251e51d"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"REVIEW_RESULT","timestamp":1784253607498957001,"uuid":"27bc59d0-1c69-4992-bd24-cbd748e35cbd"}